\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:Hero-Points"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Hero points are a metagame mechanic used to guarantee a heroic or desirable
 outcome of a particular action or event.
 The GM will grant zero or more hero points to players after each scene.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Players may spend a hero point to automatically claim success for an opposing
 skill roll, preferably described with suitable flair.
 When players spend a hero point they should describe what they are doing,
 such as a heroic move to help themselves or a party member.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Players may 
\shape italic
not
\shape default
 spend a hero point 
\shape italic
after
\shape default
 losing an opposing skill roll to change the loss to a win (this is a difference
 in how this mechanic works from most other RPGs).
 Instead, they may buy success with Debt points (see below).
 Note that this means players may have both Hero Points and Debt Points
 at the same time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Players may also spend one or more hero points (number set by the GM) to
 stave off death.
 This usually happens when the PC is Out Of The Fight and cannot prevent
 a killing blow or event.
 The GM may elect to assign one or more Injuries, so the PC doesn't feel
 he's escaped completely unscathed ...
\end_layout

