\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Optional: Starting Skill Banking
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As an optional rule, at the discretion of the GM, the players may 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

bank
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, or save, up to some maximum number of acquired skill increases at the
 start of the game for assignment at a convenient moment during play when
 knowledge of a skill becomes useful.
 The player can then permanently assign some amount of his banked points
 to a skill, effectively pretending he had them all along.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For example, John Doe's warrior has spent all but one of his initial build
 points, and after two scenes the GM has allowed him to save the two skill
 points from those scenes, giving him a total of three.
 During the next scene a situation comes up where the Climb skill would
 be useful.
 John retroactively decides that his warrior loved to climb growing up,
 and spends his three saved points on Climb, making them a permanent part
 of his PC.
\end_layout

