\begin_layout Subsection*
Minor Assist
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The priest must dramatically intone the deity's name in relevant phrase,
 such as 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Oh, GodX, heed they humble servant!
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 The priest may gain a small divine assistance: purifying food or water,
 causing a small glow to provide light, starting a campfire, etc.
 Usually may be done with relative frequency.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Ward
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The priest calmly performs a warding gesture, invoking the power of his
 deity, after which any being whose highest skill is below the priest's
 skill rank may not take offensive action against the priest.
 At Journeyman rank the priest may extend protection to his immediate area
 and chosen compatriots therein.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Assist
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A medium strength divine assistance, preferably in the theme of the deity.
 Examples would include blessing a weapon or small group before a battle;
 curing a temporary condition; speaking with the dead; exorcising a minor
 demon; minor divinations; resisting extreme environmental or elemental
 conditions; etc.
 Usually about once a day, depending on circumstances.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Divine Assistance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Significant power: major healing, including reversing permanent conditions;
 destroying major beings inimical to the deity; specific divinations, subject
 to all the vagaries typically associated with such things.
 Once a week or so.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Boon
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Serious divine intervention - small earthquake, weather control, regrowing
 lost limbs, teleportation - or a personal divine favor, not necessarily
 related to the deity's direct goals.
 While lower powers are typically rubber-stamped in normal circumstances,
 Boons and Major Workings are subject to direct approval of the diety in
 accordance with their current plans or desires, and are far more variable
 in effect ...
 if they are granted at all.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Major Working
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The kind of thing people talk about for generations: resurrection, an earthquake
 demolishing a town or castle.
 Requires extensive preparation and sacrifice, thus realistically limited
 to not more than once a year (and usually much longer).
\end_layout

