\begin_layout Standard
The Connections Skill covers all general and non-specific relationships,
 and specifically excludes anyone covered under Relationship or Member.
 Connections represents all the faceless NPCs that are not worth the player
 or GM's time to detail out.
 A PC may take this skill multiple times, once for each group or area, and
 the GM should restrict it within common sense.
 For example, 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Connections: Underworld
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, meaning 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

any underworld anywhere
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

